```java
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) return false; // 0 and negative numbers are not powers of three
        double res = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return res == (int) res; // check if log base 3 of n is an integer
    }
}
```

In this solution, we use the property of logarithms: `a^(p/q) = b` is equivalent to `loga(b) = q * loga(a)`. We check if the logarithm base 2 of the input number is an integer multiple of the logarithm base 3 of 3. If it is, then `n` is a power of 3. We cast the result of `res` back to integer and compare, as the result of logarithm may be a decimal close to an integer in case of perfect powers. If the result is a whole number, then `n` is a power of three.

